# Core Coding Standards

## Naming
- Use snake_case for functions, variables, modules
- Use PascalCase for classes
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Prefix private attributes with underscore

## Error Handling
- Never catch bare exceptions (`except:`)
- Always log exceptions with context before re-raising
- Use custom exception classes for domain errors
- Return explicit error types, not None for failures

## Imports
- Standard library first, then third-party, then local
- Use absolute imports
- No wildcard imports (`from x import *`)

## Documentation
- All public functions require docstrings (Google style)
- Module-level docstrings for non-trivial modules
- Type hints on all function signatures

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, or credentials
- Use environment variables or Secrets Manager
- Validate all external input

## File Organization
- One class per file for large classes
- Group related utilities in a single module
- Keep files under 300 lines where practical
